<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>,
                                    Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-05-08"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 8,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[40]</seg> *<hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr.
                                Roberts, the minister of Spain, late in the business hours,
                                yesterday, orally represented to this Department that he had <pb facs="0792" n="778" xml:id="pg_778"/> information to the effect
                                that the steamer Quaker City was being fitted out and armed at New
                                York for the purpose of cruising against Spanish commerce under a
                                letter of marque. I at once telegraphed to General Barlow, the
                                marshal, to inquire into the matter, with a view to further
                                proceedings. It is, however, suggested that you give him such
                                further official instructions as you may deem advisable.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to be, yours, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>HAMILTON FISH.</item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">E. R. Hoar</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Attorney-General.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>